10 [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 201.7. (a) As used in this section,
11 "permitted use" means a use that is approved in a zoning district
12 without requiring a:
13 (1) public hearing;
14 (2) variance, special exception, contingent use, or conditional
15 use; or
16 (3) discretionary zoning action, other than a determination
17 that a site plan conforms with applicable zoning regulations.
18 (b) Notwithstanding any ordinance or regulation to the
19 contrary, a confined feeding operation is a permitted use, if the
20 project or development is sited on land zoned for agricultural use.
